quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Loops[/h1]

When writing code, you may want the same block of code to run over and over again. Instead of adding several almost equal code-lines in a script, we can use [b]loops[/b] to perform a task like this.

[h2]The while Loop[/h2]

The [b]while [/b]loop executes a block of code as long as the specified condition is [b]true[/b].
[b]Syntax:[/b] [code format="php"][b]while [/b](condition is [b]true[/b]) {
   code to be executed;
}[/code]
[note]If the condition never becomes [b]false[/b], the statement will continue to execute indefinitely.[/note]

quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to print the numbers 1 to 15 to the screen.
[!raw!]
$i = 1;
while($i <= {0})   {
    echo $i;
    $i{1};
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The while Loop[/h1]

The example below first sets a variable $i to one ($i = 1). Then, the [b]while[/b] loop runs as long as $i is less than seven ($i < 7). $i will increase by one each time the loop runs ($i++): [code format="php" codeId="478"]$i = 1;
[b]while[/b] ($i < 7) {
  echo "The value is $i <br />";
  $i++;
}[/code]
